\f2\b\fs18 \cf2 \super 13\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub From Paphos,\'a0Paul and his companions sailed to Perga in Pamphylia,\'a0where John\'a0left them to return to Jerusalem.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 14\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub From Perga they went on to Pisidian Antioch.\'a0On the Sabbath\'a0they entered the synagogue\'a0and sat down.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 15\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub After the reading from the Law\'a0and the Prophets, the leaders of the synagogue sent word to them, saying, \'93Brothers, if you have a word of exhortation for the people, please speak.\'94\

\f2\b\fs18 \super 16\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Standing up, Paul motioned with his hand\'a0and said: \'93Fellow Israelites and you Gentiles who worship God, listen to me!\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 17\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub The God of the people of Israel chose our ancestors; he made the people prosper during their stay in Egypt; with mighty power he led them out of that country;\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 18\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub for about forty years he endured their conduct
\f2\b\fs16 \super [a]
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub \'a0in the wilderness;\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 19\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub and he overthrew seven nations in Canaan,\'a0giving their land to his people\'a0as their inheritance.
\f2\b\fs18 \super 20\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub All this took about 450 years.\
