\f6\i Gentiles
\f5\i0 , and in the market place every day with those who happened to be present.\'a0
\f4\b\fs18 \super 18\'a0
\f5\b0\fs24 \nosupersub And also some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers were\'a0conversing with him. Some were saying, \'93What would\'a0this\'a0idle babbler wish to say?\'94 Others, \'93He seems to be a proclaimer of strange deities,\'94\'97because he was preaching\'a0Jesus and the resurrection.\
\

\f4\b\fs18 \super 19\'a0
\f5\b0\fs24 \nosupersub And they\'a0took him and brought him to the\'a0Areopagus, saying, \'93May we know what\'a0this new teaching is which you are proclaiming?\'a0
\f4\b\fs18 \super 20\'a0
\f5\b0\fs24 \nosupersub For you are bringing some strange things to our ears; so we want to know what these things mean.\'94\'a0
\f4\b\fs18 \super 21\'a0
\f5\b0\fs24 \nosupersub (Now all the Athenians and the strangers\'a0visiting there used to spend their time in nothing other than telling or hearing something new.)\
\

\f4\b\fs18 \super 22\'a0
\f5\b0\fs24 \nosupersub So Paul stood in the midst of the\'a0
\f4\b\fs16 \super [\ul s\ulnone ]
\f5\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Areopagus and said, \'93Men of\'a0Athens, I observe that you are very\'a0religious in all respects.\'a0
\f4\b\fs18 \super 23\'a0
\f5\b0\fs24 \nosupersub For while I was passing through and examining the\'a0objects of your worship, I also found an altar with this inscription, \'91TO AN UNKNOWN GOD.\'92 Therefore what\'a0you worship in ignorance, this I proclaim to you.\
